Special/Full Revision:  For the years 2000 to 2007 the previous data for the European Union (country code 97) is replaced with data for EU27. Previously, European Union (country code 97) contained data for EU25. The data for EU27, and previously EU25, shows the trade of EU member countries with non-EU countries/areas (so called Extra EU trade). This change was necessary due to the accession of the two new member states Bulgaria and Romania to the European Union as of 1 January 2007. As additional benefit the entire time series 2000-2007 for the European Union (country code 97) now conforms with the standards and outputs of the new processing system which has been established 1 January 2006 (previously this was only the case for data of the years 2004 to 2007). The data was received from the EUROSTAT on 20 May 2008.
